            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">When you aid a friend with a task, you find many ways to help and avoid interfering. On a critical success to <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.actionspf2e\" data-id=\"HCl3pzVefiv9ZKQW\" draggable=\"true\"><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i> Aid</a>, you grant your ally a +3 circumstance bonus if you have expert proficiency in the skill (rather than +2), and you grant your ally a +4 circumstance bonus if you have master proficiency (rather than +3). If you roll a critical failure on a check to Aid, you don’t give your ally a –1 circumstance penalty to their check.</span></p>"
